ll. I haven&#8217;t tried it, so I can&#8217;t contest to how it may affect the texture. You could replace the diary milk with soy and probably have very few changes in texture, but you&#8217;ll have to find a non-dairy solid fat to use in place of the butter. All of these changes on their own probably won&#8217;t make a huge difference, but when you put them all together you may end up with a very different end product.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2013/01/chai-spiced-scones/?replytocom=71714#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-71714\", \"71714\", \"respond\", \"13087\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"comment-71719\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\"><a href='http://www.blogger.com/profile/10219805596770405058' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Rachel</a></cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2013/01/chai-spiced-scones/#comment-71719\">01.22.13 at 1:23 pm</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>Hi, Why not make them the British way by using a round cutter or using a glass &#8211; then they are even smaller?</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2013/01/chai-spiced-scones/?replytocom=71719#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-71719\", \"71719\", \"respond\", \"13087\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment odd 